c48eacfb7f307e5731688%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22942%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJamie%20Dimon%20on%20Tuesday%20addressed%20Ryland%20McClendon's%20new%20job%3Cp%3EScreenshot%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fd6e75c9-5e93-4bfd-b1eb-30f6a6759b9b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20investment%20banker's%20daughter%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMcClendon%20grew%20up%20near%20Atlanta%2C%20Georgia%20with%20her%20parents%20and%20three%20siblings.%20Her%20father%20was%20an%20investment%20banker%2C%20and%20her%20mother%20was%20a%20longtime%20public%20administrator.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20dad%2C%20Raymond%20J.%20McClendon%2C%20ran%20the%20Atlanta%20investment%20firm%20Pryor%2C%20McClendon%2C%20Counts%20and%20Co.%2C%20which%20helped%20the%20city%20of%20Atlanta%20raise%20money%20through%20the%20sale%20of%20bonds%20for%20what%20is%20now%20the%20Hartsfield-Jackson%20Atlanta%20International%20Airport%2C%20according%20to%20news%20reports%20from%20the%20early%201990s.%20The%20firm%20also%20helped%20finance%20the%20city's%20MARTA%20public%20metro%20system%2C%20which%20McClendon's%20mother%20later%20helped%20lead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcClendon's%20mother%2C%20also%20named%20Ryland%2C%20was%20named%20the%20first%20Black%20person%20and%20the%20first%20woman%20to%20chair%20Atlanta's%20public%20transit%20system%20board%20of%20directors%20in%20the%20early%201990s.%20Before%20that%2C%20she%20was%20a%20transit%20aide%20to%20Washington%20D.C.%20mayor%20Marion%20Barry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%202023%20episode%20of%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jpmorganchase.com%2Fnewsroom%2Fstories%2Fdeepa-ryland%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20JPMorgan's%20%26quot%3BWomen%20on%20the%20Move%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20podcast%2C%20McClendon%20said%20her%20career%20path%20has%20been%20heavily%20influenced%20by%20her%20parents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20went%20to%20Duke.%20I%20majored%20in%20econ%20and%20public%20policy.%20And%20where%20did%20that%20come%20from%3F%20The%20strong%20influence%20of%20my%20parents.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcClendon%20also%20said%20on%20the%20podcast%20that%20she%20enjoys%20solving%20particularly%20tricky%20problems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20the%20person%20that%20loves%20logic%20puzzles%20and%20Sudoku%20and%20all%20those%20things.%20So%20like%2C%20the%20hairier%20the%20problem%2C%20the%20more%20excited%20I%20get%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20on%20the%20podcast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22691c7854-a9b6-47f0-9fc1-74eb562453c3%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHer%20time%20as%20a%20junior%20banker%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20graduating%20from%20Duke%20in%202007%2C%20McClendon%20started%20working%20at%20SunTrust's%20investment%20banking%20arm%3A%20SunTrust%20Robinson%20Humphrey%2C%20according%20to%20her%20LinkedIn.%20There%2C%20she%20said%20on%20the%20JPM%20podcast%2C%20she%20had%20her%20own%20experiences%20feeling%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwall-street-junior-investment-bankers-burnt-out-demoralized-pandemic-2021-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efrustrated%20as%20a%20junior%20banker%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20started%2C%20the%20market%20was%20like%20this%2C%20it%20was%202007.%20Then%20it%20crashed%2C%20so%20we%20were%20all%20just%20happy%20to%20have%20jobs%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20But%20after%20the%20labor%20market%20had%20started%20to%20thaw%2C%20%26quot%3Bnobody%20was%20talking%20to%20us%20about%20getting%20promoted.%20It%20got%20to%20a%20point%20where%20it's%20really%20frustrating%20and%20everybody%20just%20said%2C%20'Oh%2C%20keep%20doing%20what%20you're%20doing%20and%20it'll%20come.'%20And%20that%20just%20didn't%20sit%20well%20with%20me.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20three%20and%20a%20half%20years%20into%20that%20job%2C%20McClendon%20explained%2C%20she%20met%20a%20JPMorgan%20banker%20at%20a%20client%20meeting%20in%20Florida.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAbout%20a%20month%20later%2C%20she%20called%20me%20up%20and%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BHey%2C%20we've%20got%20an%20associate%20role%20in%20our%20Atlanta%20office.%20Are%20you%20interested%3F%26quot%3B%20And%20I%20said%2C%20sure.%20And%20so%20I%20interviewed%20and%20got%20the%20role.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20role%20was%20in%20JPM's%20corporate%20banking%20%26amp%3B%20specialized%20industries%20team%2C%20where%20she%20began%20as%20an%20associate%20in%202010%20and%20stayed%20for%20nearly%20seven%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226218e978-9c60-4e74-bd74-2e11d14134bc%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20switch%20to%20HR%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202017%2C%20she%20moved%20to%20the%20firm's%20talent%20team%20and%20headed%20campus%20recruiting%20for%20the%20commercial%20bank%2C%20citing%20%26quot%3Borganizational%20changes%26quot%3B%20and%20learning%20that%20a%20promotion%20in%20banking%20might%20be%20further%20off%20than%20she%20had%20hoped.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20were%20some%20organizational%20changes%20happening%2C%20and%20I%20said%2C%20okay%2C%20this%20feels%20like%20a%20good%20time%20to%20kind%20of%20put%20some%20feelers%20out%20there%2C%20look%20at%20some%20other%20things%2C%20which%20I%20did%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20on%20the%20JPM%20podcast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20had%20to%20silence%20my%20ego%20a%20little%20bit.%20I%20was%20on%20this%20path%20%E2%80%A6%20a%20third-year%20VP%20in%20corporate%20banking.%20I%20was%20this%20close%2C%20I%20felt%20like%2C%20to%20getting%20my%20own%20clients%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20wasn't%20easy%2C%20and%20it%20did%20hurt.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20recalled%20calling%20up%20her%20mentor%20at%20the%20time%2C%20who%20she%20described%20as%20the%20%26quot%3Bhead%20of%20the%20business.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20said%2C%20you%20know%2C%20this%20is%20a%20long%20haul%20and%20there's%20some%20skills%20that%20kind%20of%20put%20you%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20pack%20that%20you%20may%20not%20get%20there%20in%20the%20timeframe%20you%20want%20to%20get%20there%20in.%20And%20he%20said%2C%20I'm%20saying%20this%20to%20you%20not%20to%20make%20you%20feel%20bad.%20I'm%20saying%20this%20to%20you%20because%20I%20love%20you%20and%20I%20care%20about%20you.%20I%20really%20had%20to%20listen.%20As%20much%20as%20it%20hurt%2C%20I%20kind%20of%20just%20had%20to%20let%20go%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BAnd%20I'm%20so%20glad%20that%20I%20did%20because%20it%20put%20me%20on%20a%20path%20to%20doing%20work%20that%20was%20more%20fulfilling%20for%20me%20personally%20and%20professionally%20and%20stretched%20me%20in%20different%20ways.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202019%20McClendon%20became%20head%20of%20career%20development%20programs.%20About%20two%20years%20later%2C%20she%20got%20a%20big%20call%20from%20the%20then-head%20of%20diversity%20and%20inclusion%20for%20the%20investment%20bank%2C%20who%20told%20her%20she%20had%20already%20recommended%20McClendon%20to%20replace%20her.%20She%20was%20indeed%20chosen%20for%20the%20role%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227e8183d3-9d88-43f4-9d7a-1c6b604f4049%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHeading%20DEI%20on%20Wall%20Street%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPast%20reports%20describe%20McClendon's%20mom%20as%20someone%20skilled%20in%20%26quot%3Bforming%20coalitions%26quot%3B%20and%20getting%20other%20people%20to%20her%20side%20%E2%80%94%20skills%20the%20junior%20McClendon%20appears%20to%20also%20have%20practiced%20in%20her%20role%20as%20the%20head%20of%20diversity%2C%20equity%2C%20and%20inclusion%20for%20corporate%20and%20investment%20banking%20at%20JPMorgan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%202023%20podcast%2C%20McClendon%20said%20she%20likes%20to%20use%20storytelling%20as%20a%20tool%20to%20educate%20because%20it%20can%20be%20more%20effective%20than%20numbers%20alone.%20She%20explained%20that%20when%20presenting%20to%20a%20group%2C%20for%20example%2C%20she%20likes%20to%20%26quot%3Bstrategically%26quot%3B%20insert%20stories%20in%20with%20raw%20data%20to%20make%20an%20impression.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20can%20remember%20maybe%20one%20or%20two%20facts%20and%20figures%2C%20but%20what's%20really%20going%20to%20move%20them%2C%20what%20they're%20going%20to%20be%20talking%20about%20months%20and%20even%20years%20from%20now%20is%20the%20stories%20that%20they%20hear%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20podcast%2C%20she%20went%20on%20to%20share%20a%20particularly%20defining%20experience%20she%20witnessed%20as%20a%20young%20child%20in%20her%20%26quot%3Bpredominantly%20white%26quot%3B%20neighborhood%20%E2%80%94%20a%20neighbor%20approached%20her%20then-teenaged%20older%20brother%20with%20a%20gun%20in%20front%20of%20their%20home%20after%20jumping%20to%20the%20conclusion%20that%20the%20teen%20was%20trying%20to%20steal%20her%20father's%20car.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20mom%2C%20fortunately%2C%20was%20upstairs%20and%20looked%20out%20the%20window%20and%20saw%20it.%20And%20so%20she%20raced%20downstairs%2C%20ran%20out%20the%20front%20door%20screaming%20my%20brother's%20name%20so%20that%20the%20guy%20would%20know%2C%20he%20lives%20here%2C%20we%20know%20him%2C%20this%20is%20not%20what%20you%20think%20it%20is.%20I%20was%20a%20young%20child%20at%20the%20time%2C%20but%20it%20was%20really%20eye-opening%20for%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20point%2C%20she%20said%2C%20is%20to%20use%20stories%20to%20bring%20people%20into%20each%20others'%20worlds%20and%20experiences%20%E2%80%94%20a%20tool%20she%20could%20use%20in%20her%20role%20as%20junior%20banker%20protector.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BStorytelling%20is%20the%20most%20powerful%20tool%20we%20can%20use%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjpmorgan-ryland-mcclendon-oversee-junior-bankers-wellness-80-hour-weeks-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1726778386000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F