2Fem%3Efor%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fladakh.iisdindia.in%2Ffd%2FTraditional%2520Irrigation%2520and%2520Water%2520Distribution%2520System%2520in%2520Ladakh.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Indian%20Journal%20of%20Traditional%20Knowledge%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20authors%20Dorjey%20Angchuk%20and%20Premlata%20Singh%20explain%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20melted%20snow%20water%20from%20various%20rivulets%2C%20called%20%3Cem%3Ekangs-chhu%3C%2Fem%3E%20(ice%20water)%20merging%20at%20some%20point%20forms%20a%20%3Cem%3Etogpo%3C%2Fem%3E%20(stream)%20that%20flows%20through%20a%20valley%20touching%20many%20villages%20connected%20by%20the%20channel%2C%20called%20%3Cem%3Ema-yur%3C%2Fem%3E%20(mother%20channel).%20It%20is%20built%20along%20a%20mountainside%20that%20forms%20its%20retaining%20wall%2C%20and%20is%20lined%20with%20clay%20to%20hold%20the%20water.%20This%20is%20termed%20the%20Ladakhi%20version%20of%20a%20dyke.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAt%20some%20places%20rocks%20are%20broken%20to%20allow%20the%20passage%20of%20water%20or%20else%20where%20the%20rocks%20are%20too%20hard%2C%20a%20hollow%20poplar%20or%20willow%20trunk%2C%20called%20%3Cem%3Eva-to%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20cut%20into%20two%20equal%20halves%20to%20allow%20the%20water%20easy%20passage.%20Water%20from%20the%3Cem%3E%20ma-yur%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20further%20diverted%20into%20yu-ra%20(small%20canals)%2C%20which%20irrigates%20the%20fields.%20The%20point%20from%20where%20%3Cem%3Etogpo%3C%2Fem%3E%20water%20is%20diverted%20into%20%3Cem%3Ema-yur%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20and%20%3Cem%3Ema-yur%3C%2Fem%3E%20water%20into%20%3Cem%3Eyu-ra%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20called%20%3Cem%3Eyurgo%3C%2Fem%3E%3B%20and%20ska%20is%20the%20point%20from%20where%20%3Cem%3Eyu-ra%3C%2Fem%3E%20water%20is%20diverted%20to%20the%20field.%20Water%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3Eska%20%3C%2Fem%3Eis%20further%20guided%20through%20channels%20known%20as%20%3Cem%3Esnang%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20carry%20the%20water%20into%20the%20fiel